content.description: Lay-down start with double gastons and a heel hook. A cryptic sequence of slopers and edges leads through the right side of the overhang before topping out on the slab above.
content.location: The overhang portion of the Lean-To boulder that is visible on the left side of the trail. About a minute's walk past the Point.

content.description: Stand-start, matched on the prominent jug. Climb up the face with a neat side-pull to the slopey top out.
content.location: Left of Wet Arête

content.description: SDS with right hand on a low side pull and left hand on a small undercling crimp. Powerful compression leads up and slightly right through the gently overhung feature. At the lip, head left to top out.
content.location: Left of Splash

content.description: SDS on a low right hand edge and high left. Work through edges and top out slightly right. The landing below may be wet depending on water level.
content.location: Just past Pan and Hook towards the shoreline

climbs.name: Smog Horn
climbs.fa: Unknown. First Recorded Ascent:: Will O.

content.description: Start as for Mist Maiden Low with a left hand crimp and right hand slot. Power into a large ledge before matching and finishing on Fog Horn. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Down and left of the start of Fog Horn/Mist Maiden.

content.description: SDS matched on a large flake. Move left with a series of bumps to gain a sweet rail. After the rail climb up the face on flat crimps to the top out. It should go without saying, but detached blocks are off.
content.location: Right of Hall Pass

climbs.name: Sirens' Call
climbs.fa: Unknown. First Recorded Ascent:: Will O.

content.description: Start crouched with left hand pinching the arête and right hand on a sharp crimp. Employ some body tension to gain the slopey lip and traverse left until it joins the main face. Top out. The jug above and left of the lip is off. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Left of Mist Maiden Low.

content.description: Start crouched with a left hand on side-pull and right hand on a small edge. Climb the slab with large footholds to the top out.
content.location: Right of Schoolyard Slab Left.

climbs.name: Schoolyard Arête
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded Ascent: Will O.

content.description: SDS matched on a low ledge on the far right side of the boulder. Traverse left utilizing the slopey arête and a few side-pulls on the face. Top out as for the slabs.
content.location: Right of the Schoolyard Slabs

content.description: SDS on a slightly incut edge in the center of the overhang. Move left to a side pull and then bump to a large ledge. Climb positive holds to the top.
content.location: Backside of the Lean-to boulder

content.description: SDS matched on a slopey feature on the left arête. Fight the barndoor and work up the slab to the top out. The detached block out left is off.
content.location: Left side of the slab opposite Skipping School

content.description: Lay-down start. Left hand on a large ledge and right in an incut triangle-jug. Move left to an incut ledge before highstepping with small edges in hand. Would be considerably less awkward without the birch tree right behind you, nice movement though. Detached blocks are off!
content.protection: A pad and maybe someone to pull the tree out of your way!
content.location: Backside of the boulder located on the south end of the 2nd cobble beach

content.description: SDS with right hand on an undercling edge and left on a positive ledge. Climb large edges to the top.
content.location: On the trail side of the boulder on the far right on the 2nd cobble beach.

content.description: SDS with both hands on a the large undercling. Muscle up to a decent edge before heading right to similar edges and topping out. A bit dabby in some parts, but an excellent climb nonetheless!
content.location: On the right face of the cave feature of the Lean-to Boulder (actually on the adjacent boulder).

climbs.name: Mourning Manatee
climbs.fa: Unknown. First Recorded Ascent:: Will O.

content.description: SDS with right hand on a sharp crimp and left on a vertical, flat edge. Power through the overhang to gain a positive pinch on the arête. Finish on Sirens' Call. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Down and right of Sirens' Call.

climbs.name: Mist Maiden Low
climbs.fa: Unknown. First Recorded Ascent:: Will O.

content.description: SDS with left hand gastoning a flat crimp and right in a small slot. Make a powerful move to the a big ledge, match and finish on Mist Maiden. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Down and left of Mist Maiden/Fog Horn

climbs.name: Mist Maiden
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded ascent Will O.

content.description: Stand start with left hand on a large ledge in the center of the boulder and right on an adjacent side pull. Climb up and left to a wide, slopey pinch before stabbing left to the arête. A few more moves on positive holds lead over the bulge and to the top. Nice movement in a neat feature. Detached blocks are off.There is a loose block I was unable to remove that is near the left hand starting hold (See picture), please avoid pulling on this.
content.location: Center of the boulder, same as Fog Horn

climbs.name: Maiden Voyage
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded ascent Will O. & Justus S.

content.description: Start as for Fog Horn Low, matched on the large undercling. Powerful, dynamic climbing leads into the tenuous movement of Mist Maiden. Sustained, gymnastic sequences through the most striking portion the boulder. Classic.  Detached blocks are off.There is a loose block I was unable to remove that is near the left hand starting hold (See picture), please avoid pulling on this.
content.location: Starts beneath the small roof, same as Fog Horn Low.

climbs.name: Lighthouse Traverse
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded Ascent: Will O.

content.description: Stand-start on the far right end of the boulder with right hand on a high edge and left on a sloping, near vertical rail. Climb left, following a seam of positive edges all the way to the top out of Fog Horn.
content.location: Right of Lighthouse

climbs.name: Lighthouse
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded Ascent: Sage P

content.description: SDS matched on a massive undercling in the roof. Power over the lip to a unique side-pull and a sharp crimp before executing a technical pull to jugs beneath the lip and top out. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Climbs the right side of the roof on the boulder 200' up-shore of Splash.

content.description: SDS with left hand on a small edge and right hand on a nearby side-pull. Pull off the ground, climb up the slab and top out.
content.location: Left of Splish

content.description: SDS with right hand on an edge and left on a small side pull/pinch. Come in to a left hand pinch and blast to a jug. Top out.
content.location: Far left line on the backside of the Lean-to boulder.

content.description: SDS with left hand side pull and right hand on another side pull. Climb right, into the middle section of pan and top out.
content.location: Leftmost route on the trail side of the boulder on the far right of the 2nd cobble beach

content.description: SDS with left hand on an in-cut side-pull and right on a nearby pinch. An excellent sequence leads up the arête on sloping features before rounding the corner and topping out.
content.location: Furthest left route in the corridor 50 feet south of the Lean-To Boulder.

climbs.name: Fog Horn Low
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded Ascent: Will O.

content.description: SDS match on the big undercling. Power up to a slopey yet sharp slot before blasting to a jug, working into, and finishing on the Fog Horn. Big moves on neat holds. Part of the difficulty comes from not dabbing. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Same as Light House and Dutchman's Delight

climbs.name: Fog Horn
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded Ascent: Will O.

content.description: Start sitting on the nearby rock with left hand on a large edge and right on an undercling. Work up the rounded, slopey face before stabbing to a nice in-cut and climbing ledge features to the top.
content.location: Left of Lighthouse

content.description: SDS with left hand on a small crimp in the roof and right on a positive pinch on the arête. Burly compression leads through the overhang to a difficult lip encounter before the slabby top out. A cryptic, sequential problem requiring a great deal of body tension to avoid dabbing the pads. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: The roof right of the Lighthouse Traverse.

climbs.name: Dutchman's Delight
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded ascent Alex Perz

content.description: SDS as for Lighthouse, matched on the large undercling beneath the roof. Head directly out of the roof to small crimps, before continuing to the lip. Thin and Technical. Detached Blocks are off.
content.location: Left of Lighthouse.

content.description: Sit start on crimp rail. Move up and get feet above short overhang to float through small edges to the top
content.location: Left of "Left entry" on slab

climbs.name: Bourgeois
climbs.fa: Unknown. First recorded on MP by Will O.

content.description: SDS matched on the prominent rail in the center of the overhang. Head out right to a side-pull crimp before gaining the prow. Employ some exciting footwork to surmount the lip and top out. A short climb with powerful, gymnastic movement. Classic!
content.location: The prow on the right side of the Lean-to Boulder.

content.description: Several clusters of boulders containing a higher density of challenging climbs can be found on both sides of the trail that leads beyond the point.
